author: lundblad
msg: Fix issue #2276 - 'svn info wcpath@X' or 'svn wcpath -rY' should
return repository lock.
Patch by: Alexander Thomas <alexander@collab.net>
(Tweaked by me.)
* subversion/libsvn_client/info.c
(svn_client_info): Check for a repository lock, even if the peg revision
is not specified or not HEAD.
* subversion/tests/clients/cmdline/lock_tests.py
(repos_lock_with_info): New test.
(test_list): Add repos_lock_with_info to list of tests.

author: djames
msg: * swig/include/svn_types.swg:
(apr_pool_t): Fix segfault in functions with nonstandard pool conventions
by correctly tweaking the pool reference count. (We currently don't allow
functions with nonstandard pool conventions in the SWIG bindings, but we
may choose to relax this requirement in the future.) Followup to r16200.
